You are working on Bios, a privacy-first health monitoring Android app (Kotlin + Jetpack Compose).

Key constraints:
- All health data processing happens on-device. Never send raw health data to a server.
- AES-256 encryption at rest via SQLCipher.
- Max 500 lines per file. Split before adding to files near the limit.
- One logical change per prompt. Don't refactor unrelated code.

Architecture:
- model/ — Room entities and enums
- data/dao/ — Room DAOs
- engine/ — Baseline calculation, anomaly detection, statistics
- ingest/ — HealthConnect adapter, sync workers
- alerts/ — Alert generation and condition patterns
- ui/ — Compose screens, components, theme
- privacy/ — Community aggregation, contribution workers

Patterns to follow:
- Use suspend functions and Flow for async
- Room DAOs return Flow<List<T>> for observable queries
- Business logic in engine/, not in UI or data layers
- Follow existing naming: PascalCase classes, camelCase functions

Before committing, run: ./scripts/code-quality-check.sh
